                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15212988" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Sat, 26 Mar 2016 12:47:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Section 3.2: &quot;if the field or property is annotated with&lt;br/&gt;
@MatrixParam , @QueryParam or @PathParam then an implementation MUST generate an instance of&lt;br/&gt;
NotFoundException (404 status) that wraps the thrown exception and no entity&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15212990" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Sat, 26 Mar 2016 12:51:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jim, please have the fixes for test failures supported by the specification text before changing the code&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15213879" author="ema" created="Mon, 28 Mar 2016 06:41:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing out this. There must be something else wrong, I&apos;ll have a look. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15213907" author="ema" created="Mon, 28 Mar 2016 07:09:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks it requires default.wae.mapper.least.specific=true. There is exceptionMapper hides in the deep and map exception to NotAcceptableException. Why do we set this value to false ?    &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15214164" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Mon, 28 Mar 2016 12:57:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, how is a mapper related to it ? &lt;br/&gt;
404 is what the spec requires to be returned in this case, do you see 404 ?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15217902" author="ema" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 12:40:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The mapper is the exception mapper in the test , and I need to set default.wae.mapper.least.specific=true to get this test passed. I see the not found exception. Yes, the behavior is spec compliant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15217916" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 12:49:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please provide more info. What does the test mapper do ? Why do you need to set &quot;default.wae.mapper.least.specific=true&quot;, so that this test mapper is invoked ? Is this test mapper typed on WebApplicationException or RuntimeException ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6568&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6568&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15217919" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 12:54:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So perhaps this CXF mapper should be made less specific by default...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15221492" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2016 10:05:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-opening but more clarity is needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So Jim, what is the test doing ? Do you have some custom RuntimeException exception mapper which converts NotFound mapper into 406 instead ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15229772" author="ema" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2016 06:28:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes. There is an ExceptionMapper in the test which maps exception to 406: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Provider
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;TestExceptionMapper &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;implements&lt;/span&gt; ExceptionMapper&amp;lt;Throwable&amp;gt; {

	@Override
	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; Response toResponse(Throwable throwable) {
		Writer result = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; StringWriter();
		PrintWriter printWriter = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; PrintWriter(result);
		throwable.printStackTrace(printWriter);
		&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Response.status(Status.NOT_ACCEPTABLE).entity(result.toString()).build();
	}

}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It requires default.wae.mapper.least.specific  to false to get this work. I&apos;ll close this issue and this doesn&apos;t needs a fix. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
